      },
      "source": [
        "#Assigning dependent variable as x and response varible as y\n",
        "X = data.iloc[:, 1].values\n",
        "Y = data.iloc[:, 4].values\n",
        "#Show the scatterplot\n",
        "plt.scatter(X, Y)\n",
        "plt.show()"

      "outputs": [

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "AY1zSlSuyl5c"
      },
      "source": [
        " Building the Model"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "-zL_0QhruWo8",
        "outputId": "c8fb040f-91ca-4e84-e855-12338b655712"
      },
      "source": [
        " \n",
        "#Assign m and c as 0 initially\n",
        "m = 0\n",
        "c = 0\n",
        " \n",
        "#Learning Rate and Iteration\n",
        "L = 0.00001\n",
        "epochs = 50\n",
        " \n",
        "#Number of elements in x\n",
        "n = float(len(X))\n",
        " \n",
        "#Gradient Descent \n",
        "for i in range(epochs):\n",
        "    #Currebt predicted value of y\n",
        "    ypred = m*X + c\n",
        "    \n",
        "    #Partial derivative of cost function with respect to m and c\n",
        "    dm = (-2/n) * sum(X * (Y - ypred))\n",
        "    dc = (-2/n) * sum(Y - ypred)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    #Update the current value of m and c\n",
        "    m = m - L * dm\n",
        "    c = c - L * dc\n",
        " \n",
        "#Print m and that has the lowest number of error\n",
        "print (m, c)"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "0.08323873042694489 0.0022036485248894387\n"
          ],
          "name": "stdout"
        }
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "#Making predictions with the new m and c\n",
        "ypred = m*X + c\n",

        "plt.scatter(X, Y)\n",
        "plt.plot([min(X), max(X)], [min(ypred), max(ypred)], color='red') #regression line\n",
        "plt.show()"
